<td><FONT SIZE="1" FACE="Arial, Verdana" COLOR="#ff0000">Originally posted by Night Crawler on 10-25-2000 08:43 AM<BR></FONT>
<TEXTAREA NAME="EditedMessage" ROWS=10 COLS=45 WRAP="VIRTUAL">Don't worry about the results... hey, shit happens...

 But...

 I maybe the only one here who thinks like this, but I just want to say this, so here it goes.

 Mike, I think you are working too hard... I don't really care for a full out results (but I do appreciate the effort). Really all I care for is how the match started and ended with any highlights in the middle.

 Here is an example of a what Iwrestling.com is doing:

===============

 "Billy Gunn with Chyna took on Val Venis with Steven Richards. Before the match started Eddie Guerrero came out. This distracted Gunn and Val was able to take an early advantage. Billy took advantage later in the match and Steven Richards was thrown in the ring for trying to grab his leg. Billy then took care of both of them and then hit the Fame-Asser on Val for the win."

==============

 I think people (myself anyway) would prefer results that will just do that.
 With the focus on how the match ended, not every move during the match...

 I think that instead of writting all of it down, we would prefer more constant site updates and more goodies for the players (like merchandise page, CDs featuring wrestler's theme, and other stuff)

 What does everybody think?

 Would you like to see a short passage summerizing your match, or a full detailed results (and making Mike's job difficult)

--Of course sometimes there will be run-ins and interviews that the players will write and submit, but that will be added into the results fully--

 I just want to get people's opinions about this, and try to make Mike's work a bit easier so he will have more time to deal with our angles and the site.

 Please, reply (everybody) and tell me what you think</TEXTAREA>
</td></tr>
